TITLE: Gap shares pop as company's holiday earnings blow past estimates, Old Navy returns to growth
SUMMARY: Sales at Gap's largest banner Old Navy have been down for more than a year but that trend reversed on Thursday when the retailer reported a 6% jump in revenue.

TITLE: Costco misses holiday-quarter revenue expectations despite online growth
SUMMARY: E-commerce sales grew 18.4% in the quarter compared with the year earlier.

TITLE: American Eagle unveils strategy to grow profits, takes $94 million in impairment charges for logistics business
SUMMARY: American Eagle unveiled a new strategy to boost profitable growth over the next three years by focusing on building out its brands and optimizing operations.

TITLE: Call center group Teleperformance falls 23%; CEO insists AI cannot replace human staff
SUMMARY: "The day the customer is going to be a robot, maybe AI will replace the humans," Daniel Julien told CNBC.

TITLE: Hugo Boss plunges 13% on pessimistic sales outlook
SUMMARY: Shares of Hugo Boss plunged 13% Thursday, after the company warned that it may fail to meet its 2025 sales target.

TITLE: Foot Locker shares plunge nearly 30% as retailer posts holiday loss, delays key financial target
SUMMARY: Foot Locker reported earnings as CEO Mary Dillon leads the legacy retailer through an ambitious turnaround. But some analysts say it has gone too slowly.

TITLE: Abercrombie & Fitch beats holiday estimates as sales soar again, helped by higher prices
SUMMARY: Abercrombie & Fitch has been on a rollercoaster of growth over the last year and Wall Street will be keen to see if it can sustain the momentum.

TITLE: CrowdStrike shares surge on earnings beat, strong full-year guidance
SUMMARY: CrowdStrike shares surged after the company reported a strong beat and issued better-than-expected guidance for the upcoming quarter and full year.

TITLE: Nordstrom shares fall 10% as retailer warns of potential sales declines in 2024
SUMMARY: The department store retailer said revenue for the year ahead will range from a 2% decline to a 1% gain compared with the previous year.

TITLE: Shares of Wilson tennis racket maker Amer Sports drop after first earnings report
SUMMARY: Wilson tennis racket maker Amer Sports released its first earnings report since its IPO, saying its losses narrowed.

TITLE: Target shares pop more than 12% as retailer boosts profits, despite lackluster sales forecast
SUMMARY: Target grew profits even as sales stagnated, and said it plans to launch a new membership program.

TITLE: Singapore's Sea Limited posts first profitable year amid efforts to defend market share against Lazada, TikTok
SUMMARY: Net income in 2023 was $162.7 million, as compared to a net loss of $1.7 billion in 2022.

TITLE: Daimler Truck surges 17% to record on bumper earnings, buyback announcement
SUMMARY: The German truck maker posted better-than-expected pretax earnings of 5.5 billion euros for 2023, up 39% on the previous year's 4.4 billion.

TITLE: Dell shares soar 15% after beating earnings expectations, cites rising demand for AI servers
SUMMARY: Shares of Dell Technologies popped in extended trading Thursday after the company released fourth-quarter results.

TITLE: Best Buy warns of layoffs as it issues soft full-year guidance
SUMMARY: Best Buy has been in a period of slower sales in part due to the strength of its sales during the pandemic.

TITLE: Newly listed Birkenstock beats revenue expectations on higher pricing, U.S. demand
SUMMARY: Birkenstock reported its holiday quarter results Thursday after it posted a record-breaking end to its last fiscal year.

TITLE: AB InBev profits rise despite ongoing hit from Bud Light boycott in U.S.
SUMMARY: The world's biggest brewer saw annual revenue of $59.38 billion, up 7.8% but shy of analyst expectations.

TITLE: IQiyi, the Netflix of China, posts first year of profits and says it's 'excited' about Sora-like AI
SUMMARY: Chinese video content and streaming company iQiyi CFO Wang Jun said he is "excited" about potential new business opportunities with the emergence of OpenAI's text-to-video tool Sora.

TITLE: Salesforce beats on earnings but forecasts single-digit revenue growth for the year
SUMMARY: Salesforce said revenue growth will slow to 8.6% in the new fiscal year, but revenue guidance exceeds Wall Street's estimates.

TITLE: Snowflake says Frank Slootman is retiring as CEO, stock plunges more than 20%
SUMMARY: Snowflake said CEO Frank Slootman is retiring and being replaced by Google's former ad head.

TITLE: Paramount falls short of revenue expectations but posts surprise profit, strong streaming results
SUMMARY: Paramount+ reached 67.5 million subscribers during the period, a net increase of 4.1 million, and recorded 69% revenue growth year over year.

TITLE: TJX tops earnings estimates but issues light guidance ahead of uncertain growth path
SUMMARY: Off-price giant TJX Companies, which runs TJ Maxx, Marshall's and Homegoods, saw sales rise 13% during its holiday quarter.

TITLE: Novavax stock falls 20% as vaccine maker misses quarterly estimates, sees sluggish 2024 sales
SUMMARY: Novavax narrowed its losses in the quarter compared to the same period a year ago, even as demand for Covid products continues to plummet worldwide.

TITLE: Rocket Lab says contract backlog tops $1 billion, outlines Neutron progress toward first launch
SUMMARY: Rocket Lab is making steady progress on the development of its Neutron vehicle, as it aims to launch the rocket for the first time near the end of this year.

TITLE: Hims & Hers soars 31% on rapid growth in mental health, weight loss and dermatology treatments
SUMMARY: Shares of Hims & Hers Health popped Tuesday after the company reported better-than-expected quarterly results.

TITLE: Cava stock pops after blunder leads to early earnings release
SUMMARY: The Mediterranean chain topped Wall Street's estimates for both its earnings and revenue.

TITLE: Norwegian Cruise Line reports first profitable year since 2019
SUMMARY: For the full year 2024, the company expects an adjusted profit of about $635 million, or $1.23 per share.

TITLE: Macy's posts another quarter of falling sales as it unveils strategy to get back to growth
SUMMARY: The 166-year-old department store operator got a new CEO earlier this month.

TITLE: Lowe's beats earnings estimates as sales fall â€” and the company expects revenue to slide again this year
SUMMARY: The home improvement retailer said demand has been hurt by slower housing turnover and a shift in consumer spending towards services instead of goods.

TITLE: Zoom shares jump as quarterly results beat on top and bottom lines
SUMMARY: Zoom's growth has moderated dramatically since the pandemic, and the company is projecting a revenue increase of less than 2% for the current fiscal year.
